the tubules, which is common in nephrotic syndrome.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.036118,0.074374,0.086909,0.097029,0.1021,0.10275,0.10233,0.095041,0.089085,0.083364,0.070693,0.060201],"unified_progress":[0.047129,0.066461,0.085307,0.095349,0.10094,0.10889,0.10226,0.097323,0.091908,0.083163,0.068291,0.052984]},{"section":14,"text":"That points towards kidney damage causing protein loss.","dimension":9,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.033867,0.073262,0.089255,0.096976,0.098673,0.097227,0.097665,0.092235,0.088582,0.086406,0.075634,0.070218],"unified_progress":[0.037023,0.062492,0.07755,0.088721,0.094695,0.099456,0.098091,0.096791,0.096197,0.093243,0.084924,0.070817]},{"section":15,"text":"Now, considering her Hodgkin's lymphoma, could the kidney issue be related?","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.041984,0.080838,0.093116,0.097821,0.09738,0.095847,0.092494,0.08918,0.084969,0.086355,0.073345,0.066672],"unified_progress":[0.062922,0.085342,0.086544,0.090913,0.091589,0.09144,0.091244,0.090844,0.087013,0.085243,0.075149,0.061759]},{"section":16,"text":"Sometimes malignancies can cause paraneoplastic syndromes, or maybe the lymphoma is directly affecting the kidneys.","dimension":9,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.032127,0.067986,0.081931,0.091724,0.098442,0.10246,0.10175,0.097447,0.092616,0.089395,0.078555,0.065562],"unified_progress":[0.051901,0.077074,0.084778,0.088399,0.091995,0.09669,0.094662,0.095374,0.091618,0.088195,0.077621,0.061693]},{"section":17,"text":"But the more common link here is that treatments for lymphoma, like chemotherapy (e.g., alkylating agents), can cause kidney damage.","dimension":11,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.037925,0.07319,0.083157,0.090805,0.096416,0.10166,0.099031,0.09636,0.090278,0.089043,0.076782,0.06535],"unified_progress":[0.069809,0.092667,0.090776,0.090645,0.090815,0.093541,0.090285,0.090809,0.084242,0.080